'''TEDxLima''' is an independent [[TEDx]] event held annually in [[Lima]], Peru. Like other TEDx events, the event obtained a free license from [[TED (conference)|TED]] to hold the conference, with organizers agreeing to follow certain principles.<ref>{{cite news | url= https://www.nytimes.com/2010/09/26/fashion/26TEDX.html | first=Stephanie | last=Rosenbloom | | title=A Conference Makes Learning Free (and Sexy) | work=[[The New York Times]] | date=24 September 2010|accessdate=6 October 2018}}</ref> In 2017, TEDxLima received over 15,000 applications and hosted 9 speakers at the [[University of Lima]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Thomas |first1=Rachel |title=Hasbro toy designer among list of TEDxWellington speakers |url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/92717745/Hasbro-toy-designer-among-list-of-TEDxWellington-speakers |accessdate=6 October 2018 |work=[[Stuff.co.nz]]}}</ref> In 2018, TEDxLima received over 20,000 applications and hosted 9 speakers at the [[JW Marriott Hotel]] Lima.
==History== TEDxLima was founded as an independent [[TEDx]] event. In 2017, TEDxLima received over 15,000 applications and hosted 9 speakers at the [[University of Lima]]. In 2018, TEDxLima received over 20,000 applications and hosted 9 speakers at the [[JW Marriott Hotel]] Lima.
